place.name: TALBENNI
place.gazetteerText: TALBENNY, a parish in Haverfordwest district, Pembroke; on the coast, 7 miles WSW of Haverfordwest r. station. Post town, Haverfordwest. Acres, 1,425. Real property, £1,425. Pop., 204. Houses, 42. The property is much subdivided. The living is a rectory, annexed to West Walton. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
